      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo, i'm stuck on this problem on a contest site. the constraints are super tight and the judge keeps throwing Memory Limit Exceeded (MLE) on my solutions. i don't care if the code is \"clean\" or \"elegant\" or whatever, i just need it to pass the test cases. the memory limit is only 64MB and the time limit is 1.0s. can u solve this?\n\nProblem: \"Path of Least Resistance\"\nGiven an N x M grid (where N, M <= 5000) filled with non-negative integers, find the shortest path from (0,0) to (N-1, M-1) moving only right or down. \n\nThe issue is that a standard `int dp[5000][5000]` table uses like 100MB, which is way over the 64MB limit. Everything i try is hitting the MLE. Just give me a solution that gets the 'Accepted' status.",
